# Project Language: English Only

All text written in this project — including code, comments, docstrings, commit messages, documentation, variable names, function names, class names, and any user-facing content — must be in **English only**.

**Always respond in English. Do not use any other language.** This applies to all agent chat output, including explanations, summaries, feedback, and questions directed at the user.

## Enforcement

- Variable names, function names, class names, struct names, interface names, and enum values: use English identifiers (e.g., `authContext`, `sliceAuthentication`, not `contextoDeAutenticacao` or `切片认证`).
- Comments and inline documentation: English only.
- Strings and user-facing messages: English only.
- Log messages: English only.
- Error messages and problem details: English only.
- Configuration file values (keys, descriptions): English only.
- Agent chat: English only. Always respond in English. Do not use any other language.

## Rationale

Consistent use of English across the entire codebase ensures readability for international contributors, compatibility with tooling (spell checkers, linters, static analysis), and a uniform developer experience.

## Exceptions

- Literal values that must match external specifications (e.g., 3GPP XML/YAML tags, ASN.1 OIDs, API field names from standards bodies) are exempt.
- Test fixtures and seed data that represent real subscriber data in a localized context are exempt, provided they are clearly labeled.
